{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567379","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567379"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T00:00:48+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T00:00:48+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18968"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18968","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18968"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.89,0.02,0,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11702"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"110292"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11702","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11702"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18968"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92563"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"18"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4977"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"4989"},{"type":"tags","id":"4990"},{"type":"tags","id":"5715"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11410"},{"type":"tags","id":"11411"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27529"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27530"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44857"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"110292","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/110292"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EVoluntary assisted dying legislation has been enacted in several Australian states. This allows eligible persons to request medical assistance to end their life under specific circumstances.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is a mandatory requirement for accessing voluntary assisted dying in Australia?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Family member consent obtained","Decision-making capacity and voluntary request","Advanced care directive completed within previous year","Religious or cultural exemption","Psychiatric assessment clearance"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe fundamental requirement for voluntary assisted dying is that the person has \u003Cstrong\u003Edecision-making capacity and makes a voluntary request\u003C/strong\u003E without coercion. This ensures the person can make an informed choice and understands the consequences of their decision.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAdvanced care directive completed within previous year\u003C/strong\u003E - While advance care planning is important, it is not mandatory for voluntary assisted dying.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFamily member consent obtained\u003C/strong\u003E - The decision belongs to the person alone; family consent is not required.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPsychiatric assessment clearance\u003C/strong\u003E - While mental health assessment may be requested if there are concerns, it is not mandatory for all cases.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReligious or cultural exemption\u003C/strong\u003E - No exemptions are required; the choice is based on personal values.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAdditional requirements include having a terminal illness or neurodegenerative condition with death expected within 6-12 months, experiencing intolerable suffering, and assessment by two independent medical practitioners. The person must be an Australian citizen or permanent resident and meet minimum age requirements.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Voluntary assisted dying requires the person to have decision-making capacity and make the request voluntarily without coercion.","The person must have a terminal illness or neurodegenerative condition with intolerable suffering and death expected within 6-12 months.","Two independent medical practitioners must assess eligibility and confirm the person understands the consequences of their decision."],"references":["QUT. End of Life Law in Australia - Voluntary Assisted Dying. [online]. 2024. [Cited 2025 Jan 21]. Available at: https://end-of-life.qut.edu.au/assisteddying","Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 21]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92563"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18968"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92563","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/92563"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-29T15:10:38+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-29T15:10:38+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11702"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"110292"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"18","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/18"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddd1\u200d\u2696\ufe0f","name":"Medicolegal","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"headin